<section id="provenance_module">
    <title>Provenance Module</title>
    <section>
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>This module describes how to include provenance information related to the nature and
            origin of the localization data or process.</para>
        <para>Provenance information is important for the localization process itself, as it helps
            to document the different steps involved. It can also facilitate the potential reuse of
            localized material. Such reuse may take the form of a translation memory, where key
            provenance details, such as the translation date or the agents involved (people and/or
            tools) can be retrieved. This information may also be crucial for training other
            products (such as LLMs) that rely on XLIFF files as part of their training data.</para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Module Namespace and Validation Artifacts</title>
        <para>The namespace for the Provenance module is:
                <code>urn:oasis:names:tc:xliff:pvn:2.3</code></para>
        <para>XML Schema is available at …</para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Module Fragment Identification Prefix</title>
        <para>The fragment identification prefix for the Provenance module is:
            <code>pvn</code></para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Module Specification</title>
        <para>The Provenance module defines 4 elements and 9 attributes that enable the embedding of
            provenance metadata directly within XLIFF CORE elements. In the XLIFF context,
            provenance data is usually associated with two key aspects: the origin of the source
            content and the information about the localisation process applied to it. For example,
            it will allow you to include information about when the original content was extracted,
            when it was translated or who undertook that task.</para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Module Elements</title>
        <para>The elements defined in the provenance module are <olink
                targetdoc="../elements/provenance/change.xml" targetptr="change"
                    ><code>&lt;change&gt;</code></olink>, <olink
                targetdoc="../elements/provenance/provenance.xml" targetptr="provenance_element"
                    ><code>&lt;provenance&gt;</code></olink>, <olink
                targetdoc="../elements/provenance/usage.xml" targetptr="usage"
                    ><code>&lt;usage&gt;</code></olink> and <olink
                targetdoc="../elements/provenance/value.xml" targetptr="provenance_value"
                    ><code>&lt;value&gt;</code></olink></para>
        <section>
            <title>Tree Structure</title>
            <para>Legend:</para>
            <simplelist type="vert">
                <member>1 = one</member>
                <member>+ = one or more</member>
                <member>? = zero or one</member>
                <member>* = zero, one or more</member>
            </simplelist>

            <programlisting format="linespecific">
            
<olink targetdoc="../elements/provenance/provenance.xml" targetptr="provenance_element">&lt;provenance&gt;</olink>
        |
        +---<olink targetdoc="../elements/provenance/change.xml" targetptr="change">&lt;change&gt;</olink>
            |
            +---<olink targetdoc="../elements/provenance/value.xml" targetptr="provenance_value">&lt;value&gt;</olink>
            |
            ?---<olink targetdoc="../elements/provenance/usage.xml" targetptr="usage">&lt;usage&gt;</olink>
            
        </programlisting>
            <xi:include href="../../elements/provenance/provenance.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>
            <xi:include href="../../elements/provenance/change.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>
            <xi:include href="../../elements/provenance/usage.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>
            <xi:include href="../../elements/provenance/value.xml"
                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>
        </section>
    </section>

